        "rating": 5,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "a year ago",
        "text": "I've been interacting with Chapter 1 for the past four years and I can proudly say they've exceeded all of my expectations. My first child attended for four years, and my second child was there two years.\n\nThe staff are incredibly kind and loving to the children, and it was heartwarming to see the bonds my children created with them. Importantly, staff is generally very consistent without much turnover so you can count on stability for your child.\n\nThe Daycare layout was one of the key reasons I chose Chapter 1 back in 2018. Rather than individual enclosed rooms, it is one big wide open room, separated by low walls, bookcases, and gates. I liked the fact that caretakers were able to look over at one another, for reasons that: 1) caretakers could easy signal for help if they need support from coworkers, and 2) less private spaces = more personal security for a child. (Bonus: it was also nice that my eldest could hear her sibling, look over at him, and support him on his hard days if needed.)\n\nWe got lots of art daily, my kids learned a ton and are well set up for their next schooling endeavours, and as parents we felt very involved throughout the years. The staff went above and beyond to host holiday and milestone events with kids & parents, and I will very much miss being part of the Chapter 1 family.\n\nThank you so much for everything you've done for my kids and family. ",
