        "text": "Disorganized and rude staff, old facilities with dirty run down carpets. The way they respond to negative reviews is exactly the way they treat parents if any issues are brought up. They will \"deny registration\" and ask you to find another daycare for your child giving you a \"sufficient notice\" of 3 days to make new arrangements. They expected us to pay a daily drop in of $50 during those days. First day they didn't expect my 1 year old. There was confusion and unattended parents and babies at the main door. My son was handed to the toddler's room caregiver and only one caregiver was looking after 7 babies in the babies area. They seemed understaffed. The toddler and baby areas were not separated by any structure and toddlers just run around everywhere. I noticed all the babies were in high chairs the entire time I was there (45 min and it wasn't during a meal), and my husband said he found them in the chairs in the afternoon too when he picked him up. Perhaps a byproduct of being short staffed that day? or the fact that the babies and toddler room are one and the same and there is no way for babies to walk around safely or sit on the floor. It made me wonder how long my baby sat in the chair the whole day. I emailed the director and stressed that Alberta requires a max of 4 babies per caregiver. They said they were compliant with that rule and that first day of the month is usually busier, hence the confusion. I went with it and sent him in again next day, but had the exact same experience. In the afternoon he came back and threw up his lunch. I emailed her and asked her to investigate and that in the meantime I would pack his food. She responded that that was prohibited (it's not allowed, explained to me as almost a breach in the law!?!) and that due to my son's \"high developmental needs\" they could not receive him anymore. She gave me 3 days to find a new daycare! She also said they would charge me $50 daily from that day on (they did refund me in full for the first month tho). I have a full time job and scrambled to find a new place for him but I am so glad I did. I didn't feel my baby was safe or happy at this daycare",
