        "text": "I worked as an speech and language aid for certain kids (through another company) at Fueling Brains West 85th for the entire 2022-2023 school year. Here are some alarming things I noticed that I want to share with parents if they plan on or already have their kids enrolled in this school.\n\n1. Kids are not looked after and there are MULTIPLE safety hazards. Many times while doing speech activities with my assigned children, I would have to jump in to make sure the kid jumping of the table didn‚Äôt break his head open, or get I would have to get a kid away from trying to break a glass jar. Often, there were too many kids in a classroom (up to 48 children with 6 teachers) for the teachers to pay attention to important safety issues the kids were having. Kids regularly got hurt at this facility.\n\n2. Kids hit, punch, bite, kick, and hurt each other daily. Most teachers would not notice these instances, again because there are so many kids in the classroom, and if they were noticed, sometimes the wrong kid would get in trouble. This is pretty dangerous, and again, I would sometimes jump in (during my speech activities) to help the safety of the children even though it was not my job.\n\n3. Teachers would often yell at the children and use harsh words with them. This is because there was always so much going on and the teachers were frustrated, but it still gave the wrong message to the children.\n\n4. Super high staff turn over. In the 1 year I was there, I saw between 15-25 teachers leave, and only 5 or 6 were there from the beginning of the year to the end of the year. The environment of the school is quite stressful and exhausting, so teachers get burned out easily.\n\nWith all this said, I think it would be a good idea to keep away from Fueling Brains, as I was genuinely concerned for children's safety and well-being while at the school.",
