        "rating": 1,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "6 years ago",
        "text": "Parents beware!\nJust straight facts!  I will try to be objective as much as possible.\nThe facility where the daycare is located is rented out for social functions such as weddings and parties over the weekends or in summer time. After all, you do not have to go any further than to read some of the comments from individuals who rented the premises.\n\nThe daycare itself is located at the church basement with little or no daylight.\n\nIn the late fall of 2016 when I came to bring my child I saw daycare workers cleaning up the mess that was left by renters who rented the premises over the weekend!  The hall was rented by Bulgarian community  members tho just had too much alcohol and were unable to control themselves.  I have nothing against Bulgarian community at all, but I am just basing my statement on what the daycare workers said to me.\n\nAs I discovered that day,  my daughters' shoes were missing and were nowhere to be found. Her clothing was all over the place. In addition there was broken furniture that the daycare workers were trying to fix. The place was dirty. The janitor The  daycare workers were trying to do the damage control by saying that there was nothing wrong and that the problems will be taken care of.\nThe next day the premises were cleaned up and looked OK, however I have a problem having children staying in the bar or place where alcohol is consumed and who knows what kind of drunks who may be carrying all sorts of diseases attended.\nMy older daughter was infected with wart and we still have problem having it cured to this day.\nLastly, I also saw that the daycare workers were working while having flu and were very sick. On a few occasions there were only a a few children at the daycare as many of them were became infected with flu.\n\nIn 2016 this daycare had problems attracting new children to attend. The quality of education is not bad, but what is the point of having educated but sick children?\n\nThese are the things that I personally witnessed. I want the facts to speak for themselves.\nI would like to have the reader to arrive with his/her own conclusions.",
