        "text": "PLEASE BEWARE . I up until recently had two of my children attended this \"daycare\". Back story I had I my boys enrolled in the \"daycare\" for about 3.5 years. The first, 2ish years were great my kids were happy, staff around was consistent. Communication with the workers was great.\n\nThere seem to be a change in management roughly a year ago. That's were things took a turn for the worst. My youngest (4) son in that time became so unhappy and frustrated that he was \"lashing out\" at the center. So i tried to work together with the current manager to come up with a plan she her self said the daycare was not up to standard. To rectify the situation a plan was made and improvements seem to be happening, well was I ever wrong.\n\nThe constant staff change with no follow through on the plan (there part) my son began to slip again. This time around the manager would become extremely rude on the phone and in person. She would call ordering us to pick up are son. Which we complied with. She would send a video of my son crying very distraught and upset like a video that would break your heart if it was your child. The puzzling factor was my son would not act like this at home.\n\n3 days before I started back at school we recieved a termination letter from current manager. In hindsight it was the best/only good thing she did for my child.\n\nDigging a little deeper we found out through staff and other kids. That my son was being bullied. He was being constantly singled out by some of the workers calling him a bad boy, and the staff would Tell the other children. Do not play with him as he is a bad kid. This is basic BULLYING\n\nI was heartbroken I couldn't believe as a parent I failed my own child. I actually believed the manager (current). It turns out she did not have the best interest in my child. It made me sick to my stomach when I found all this out.\n\nThe number of infractions is actually incomprehensible. Some of the most basic things were violated. Having cleaning supplies under the toddler bathroom sink. Not enough staff supervision in rooms. You can actually look these up as they are available to the public.\n\nThankfully I have both my sons in a new daycare that actually cares for there well being. The amount of change in my youngest son since the new daycare is so much. I couldn't be happier. He is getting back to his old self finally.\n\nIt's funny how when we drive by the old daycare he gets scared, nervous and always ask me if he has to go to the old \"daycare\". I just turn to him and tell him he will never go back to that daycare. You can see how relieved he is when I tell him that.\n\nNow, I know that she will respond and try to slander my review that is just how they roll at this \"daycare\". But thats a bully mentality.\n\nSincerely Kyle",
