        "text": "We were waitlisted for the Oxford location and was contacted as a spot had opened up. Did the tour, the facility is okay. Programming looks great etc etc. That's what the 2 stars are for. The problem I have was the admin and follow up. After sending in some questions after the tour via email, they were promptly answered and it was communicated a registration package will be sent our way. When the registration is completed, a welcome package will then be forwarded. We were excited that we had an opportunity at our first pick facility. So, we stopped searching and declined other opportunities that contacted us as we didn't want to hold up spots for other parents waitlisted at those other places. I guess that's where our mistake was made, we put all our eggs in one basket. We never received a registration package from Kepler, even after following up and are now searching, again, for quality child care. Good times. It's been a few weeks since any communication or reply.  What's the point of having your customer service rep and client experience lead cc'd on the email communications only to be ghosted? At least one of you have the professionalism to email back whatever the issue was. Isn't that the point of your roles, to follow up on the experience or service that is being rendered? I've gone back and forth about posting this review. However, I'm also in a high level admin role and know how these processes work and this is just terrible. Just poor consideration of a family's time and effort looking for child care when it's already not easy to do.",
