        "rating": 1,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "3 years ago",
        "text": "So disappointing. I enroll my kids in this daycare because was on front of the school.\nThis was July 2019, Chloe, the director email me the prices and how much it will be starting on September after the yearly price adjustment and summer break time. On September, the amount withdraw from my account was higher that agreed so I asked what happened. By that time, the director was Tam and she asked me for the emails.\nI sent all the emails exchanged with Chloe stating the price and she reply that was a mistake from the previous director and accounting agreed to do a 1 time discount, but they couldn't respect the price given.\nWell, on December 3rd I was notified at 7pm by Jackie Winter, Senior Are Manager that the center will close on December 13th and they will transfer all the kids to a different one, 20 min away from that one. A daycare that has been running for 20+ years, no caring for the problems this would carry.\nAs there are no other daycares that work with my kids school, we agreed.\nOn January 30 I gave my 1 month notice to take my kids to somewhere else as the distance is killing our days. Next day we receive a call asking what they could do for us to keep the kids in the center, that they could offer us a great discount, but honestly, the distance is stronger than the money, so we refuse.\n2 days later, Jackie email me saying I'm owning them money the Subsidy didn't cover in October.\nI not even have subsidy...I forwarded her all the emails of why I do got a one time discount and she never replies.\nNow my kids are somewhere else, I'm receiving emails trying to charge me this mystery amounts.\nI tried to call the main office in Ontario and no one answer ever, the current site director (because no one seem to last over 3 months) said she want me to send all the emails again.\n\nPlease avoid the headache, this franchise is so poorly managed and they close the daycare no caring for the effect on the kids or parents.\nMy friend in BC had the same situation, they close a center from one day to another.",
