        "text": "I heard about Kids and Company from my boss at the time. We checked them out and I am so glad we did.\nWe really liked the fact that we could check in on our daughter on their webcams. Which, by doing so we saw some things that gave us cause for concern. We brought them up to the director and she was FANTASTIC. She took our concerns very seriously and acted immediately on them to correct them. She also kept me informed throughout the process.\nWe also brought a concern up to the assistant director about the angle of the camera and how we couldn't see a corner of the classroom very well. She immediately looked at it and corrected it while I was there.\nNow what we see is fantastic staff engaging with my daughter and the children in her classroom.\nI used to be worried as a first time mom leaving my daughter in the hands of strangers as I didn't know what level of care she would receive but I do not worry anymore. I know she is in GREAT hands. It shows by the enthusiasm my daughter has when she comes to this place.\nMy daughter used to cling to me and cry when I tried to pass her off to the teacher, because it was a new experience for her, but now she almost jumps out of my arms to go to the teacher, Joy or Claudia when I drop her off! She sometimes even waves goodbye to me, which makes me very happy to see she is comfortable with the ladies there!\nYou can tell all of the staff love the children that go there, that its not just a job to them. The staff know all the childrens names as they pass in the hall, whether they are in the same classroom or not.\nWe are even buying a house in the same area (even though we wanted to go further south) so that we didn't have to find a new daycare.\nI highly recommend this daycare!!",
