        "relativeTimeDescription": "a year ago",
        "text": "My daughter has been attending Lakewood daycare for 2 years, and I'm looking forward to sending my infant in a couple of months. As a mother and a psychologist with over 15 years of experience (which includes advanced training at the University of Alberta, a competitive and accredited program) I would highly recommend this daycare. Our experience with teacher Rebecca was more than we could ask for. Our daughter is a strong willed and sensitive child, and it can take a lot of time for her to warm up to someone. She immediately established a bond with Rebecca. She is no longer in that classroom, and she will tell us every week she wants to be in teacher Rebecca room. Over the years I observed Rebecca create a safe space (physical and emotional), while also developing an age appropriate curriculum. My child has learned so much from Rebecca and we are grateful for that. Recently there have been some concerning reviews about Rebecca that are not consistent with my experience or the other parents I have talked to. Professionally speaking, I disagree that this daycare would lead to childhood trauma. This is a reputable daycare with over ten years of the same management. This daycare has seen repeat customers and many families find their way there through word of mouth. Finding a child care provider is one of the biggest decisions you will make as a parent. I hope in addition to looking at online reviews, you will talk to the owner, staff and other parents when making this decision. I would be happy to talk to anyone that is curious about this business from a parent perspective but also a child development perspective.",
