        "rating": 5,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "2 years ago",
        "text": "This review is for the south side location. I‚Äôve had the pleasure of sending 2 of my children from 12 months old all the way through to OSC care up to grade 3 and pre-school. I made a surprise visit when first considering this daycare and they served healthy veggie snacks and the director was also hands on & they gladly gave me the grand tour. I was lucky there was no waiting list at the time either. Their pricing is competitive and, I dare say more affordable than some others. They were excellent at offering tips on how to reduce separation anxiety at drop offs when we first started and as my kids developed, they had communication sheets/ books so I could read on the progress and they posted photos on the walls so I didn‚Äôt feel like I was missing out ( I work full time). They staff are great at communication and were always quick to call if my child was ill or if an incident happened with another child, their follow up processes are excellent. They post everything too, everything from audits, fire drill results, if there was COVID exposures (rare), first aid qualified staff, resources for parents, and even what the daily menus are for the kids (I really appreciated how they served healthy meals and hot lunches). Their programs offerings are excellent and included other fun things like kid yoga, and even Zumba at one point. They‚Äôve had community guest speakers like police and firemen, and even did neighborhood field trips to the seniors centre & the grocery store pre-pandemic and did Halloween trick or treating with the shops on the same strip mall. They also do outdoor walks, trips to the playground and even silver berry park/playground sometimes. Their teaching programs in general are fantastic, my youngest learned the names of continents through song at age 4 and the special days like teddy bear picnics, or multicultural days are fun & taught my kids about ethnic traditions re: my eldest had learned a Punjabi kids rhyme (we‚Äôre not Punjabi), and they learned about Diwali, Chinese New Year, etc. We opted for the summer camp preschool program this year while my youngest transitioned to a new daycare within the school she‚Äôs starting at this fall and MMSSCDC did direct pick up & drop off with her for their day amp program. I feel like this daycare has been like a second parent to my children and they have raised them so well. It‚Äôs a little bittersweet having to leave, we just found it more convenient for a direct drop off and pick up at their school for OSC who are open just a little bit earlier and closed later, even though I feel the service is not up to par and not as good a value compared to MMSSCDC (now called scholastic). If and when I have another child, MMSSCDC will definitely be the top choice for daycare in my books!!",
