        "rating": 5,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "2 months ago",
        "text": "An absolutely AMAZING place! We have sent all 3 of our children to Riverbend Montessori Child Development Centre over the last 8 YEARS!! We started them at Riverbend Montessori when they were 2 and 3. The staff, the atmosphere, play areas, and other children are wonderful. If you are looking for a new place to send your children, this place is EXCELLENT. Our children learned, played, and their social skills increased so well as they grew. We loved the field trips, bike days, activities, nature walks, park days, ice cream days, birthday celebrations, sledding, Christmas concerts, celebrations of all cultural events, and many creations our children made here. We especially loved the updates and photos  we would get of our children of their activities during the day. They especially helped our last child adjust to going to Riverbend Montessori so well. He would cry when I left him, most likely because I took an extended maternity leave and he‚Äôs my baby ! (He is super attached to me). But Teacher Mylene would always be there to comfort him, and ensure he felt safe and cared for. Our family will always be forever grateful to Pam, Mylene, Mama Sana, Shazia, Susan (who have been there from day 1), and all the Riverbend Montessori staff. They treated all our children like their own family.\n\nSide comment to the lady LB who only gave a one star rating because she didn‚Äôt want to pay the administration fee to hold a spot on the wait list. This DOES NOT reflect the quality of the business and does not justify one star. It takes a lot to maintain a business (the admin, planning, scheduling etc.). When you apply to the University of Alberta you have to pay an application fee to show you are SERIOUS to attend. Many places have an administrative fee. This is no different. If 100 people asked to be put on the wait list and only 30 were serious to attend, that adds up to a lot of time and energy calling people back and confirming a spot for them. If you just want a regular ‚Äúdaycare‚Äù with no fee, then that‚Äôs your choice. Go find one. But I can definitely say your child will not have the same  amazing care and experiences they would have received, if they had attended Riverbend Montessori. If you are serious, the admin fee is just a stepping stone to get your child into an AMAZING program, with amazing people, and other amazing children!",
